 Police in Lagos State have arraigned Chidinma Pearl Ogbulu, a businesswoman who distributed kegs of petrol as souvenirs at a recent ceremony held at Havilah Events Centre, Victoria Island on March 4. Ogbulu was arraigned on Monday at the Special Offences (Mobile) Court of Lagos State in the Ikeja Magisterial District, Holden at Oshodi. She faced four counts of conduct likely to cause a breach of peace, endangering human life by distributing combustible matter in a public gathering, intent to harm another and unlawfully carrying on the business of storage and containerising petroleum product without a permit. Her arrest followed the viral video of the distribution of petrol as a souvenir recently. Abiodun Alabi, Commissioner of Police in Lagos State ordered the arrest of the suspect who was initially at large. Warning citizens against acts capable of endangering human lives, the CP said that the command remained committed to protecting lives and property. 